{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775895040682,"sessionID":"ses_28468a2b8ffeCdGYvhIGS4WTXI","part":{"id":"prt_d7b97cf57001AXxZ8n2PgCw9cn","messageID":"msg_d7b97acae001WxkXj5RiY5xiH8","sessionID":"ses_28468a2b8ffeCdGYvhIGS4WTXI","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-9bc7dd542a4c45d9ab2dc398450801d6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/example/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/example/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-037: PCAP Analyzer Example Application\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: A Python example application demonstrating AgentCube SDK usage for PCAP (packet capture) file analysis. The application uses `CodeInterpreterClient` to execute network analysis tools and Python scripts in an isolated sandbox environment.\n6: \n7: | Attribute | Value |\n8: |-----------|-------|\n9: | Module | example |\n10: | Language | Python |\n11: | Size | M |\n12: | SDK | agentcube-sdk |\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Architecture\n17: \n18: ### Directory Structure\n19: \n20: ```\n21: example/\n22: ├── pcap-analyzer/\n23: │   ├── design.md              # This document\n24: │   ├── spec.md                # Specification\n25: │   ├── main.py                # Entry point\n26: │   ├── analyzer.py            # Core analyzer logic\n27: │   ├── parsers/\n28: │   │   ├── __init__.py\n29: │   │   ├── tcp_parser.py      # TCP stream parser\n30: │   │   ├── http_parser.py     # HTTP traffic parser\n31: │   │   └── dns_parser.py      # DNS query parser\n32: │   ├── utils/\n33: │   │   ├── __init__.py\n34: │   │   ├── file_utils.py      # File handling utilities\n35: │   │   └── report_utils.py    # Report generation\n36: │   ├── requirements.txt       # Dependencies\n37: │   ├── README.md              # Usage documentation\n38: │   └── tests/\n39: │   │   ├── test_analyzer.py\n40: │   │   ├── test_tcp_parser.py\n41: │   │   └── test_http_parser.py\n42: │   └── sample_data/\n43: │   │   ├── sample.pcap        # Sample PCAP file for testing\n44: │   │   └── expected_output.json\n45: ```\n46: \n47: ### Component Diagram\n48: \n49: ```\n50: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n51: │                        PCAP Analyzer Example                              │\n52: ├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n53: │                                                                          │\n54: │   ┌─────────────────┐                                                    │\n55: │   │    main.py      │                                                    │\n56: │   │  (CLI Entry)    │                                                    │\n57: │   └────────┬────────┘                                                    │\n58: │            │                                                             │\n59: │            ▼                                                             │\n60: │   ┌─────────────────┐     ┌───────────────────────────────────────┐     │\n61: │   │   analyzer.py   │────▶│        AgentCube SDK                  │     │\n62: │   │                 │     │  ┌─────────────────────────────────┐  │     │\n63: │   │  - load_pcap()  │     │  │    CodeInterpreterClient        │  │     │\n64: │   │  - analyze()    │     │  │                                 │  │     │\n65: │   │  - generate_    │     │  │  - execute_command()            │  │     │\n66: │   │    report()     │     │  │  - run_code()                   │  │     │\n67: │   └────────┬────────┘     │  │  - upload_file()                │  │     │\n68: │            │              │  │  - download_file()              │  │     │\n69: │            ▼              │  └─────────────────────────────────┘  │     │\n70: │   ┌─────────────────┐     └──────────────────┬────────────────────┘     │\n71: │   │    parsers/     │                        │                          │\n72: │   │                 │                        ▼                          │\n73: │   │  - tcp_parser   │     ┌───────────────────────────────────────┐     │\n74: │   │  - http_parser  │     │          Sandbox Pod                   │     │\n75: │   │  - dns_parser   │     │  ┌─────────────────────────────────┐  │     │\n76: │   └────────┬────────┘     │  │           PicoD                 │  │     │\n77: │            │              │  │                                 │  │     │\n78: │            ▼              │  │  - tshark CLI                   │  │     │\n79: │   ┌─────────────────┐     │  │  - tcpdump CLI                  │  │     │\n80: │   │    utils/       │     │  │  - Python runtime               │  │     │\n81: │   │                 │     │  │  - scapy library                │  │     │\n82: │   │  - file_utils   │     │  │  - pyshark library              │  │     │\n83: │   │  - report_utils │     │  └─────────────────────────────────┘  │     │\n84: │   └─────────────────┘     └───────────────────────────────────────┘     │\n85: │                                                                          │\n86: └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n87: ```\n88: \n89: ### Flow Diagram\n90: \n91: ```\n92: ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n93: │                         PCAP Analysis Flow                                 │\n94: ├───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n95: │                                                                            │\n96: │   1. Initialize                                                            │\n97: │   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n98: │   │  Client = CodeInterpreterClient(                                     │ │\n99: │   │      name=\"pcap-analyzer\",                                           │ │\n100: │   │      ttl=3600                                                        │ │\n101: │   │  )                                                                   │ │\n102: │   └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n103: │                                                                            │\n104: │   2. Upload PCAP                                                           │\n105: │   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n106: │   │  client.upload_file(\"traffic.pcap\", \"/workspace/traffic.pcap\")       │ │\n107: │   └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n108: │                                                                            │\n109: │   3. Run Analysis Scripts                                                  │\n110: │   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n111: │   │  # Use tshark to extract fields                                      │ │\n112: │   │  client.execute_command(                                             │ │\n113: │   │      \"tshark -r traffic.pcap -Y tcp -T fields ...\"                   │ │\n114: │   │  )                                                                   │ │\n115: │   │                                                                      │ │\n116: │   │  # Run Python analysis                                               │ │\n117: │   │  client.run_code(\"python\", analyze_script)                           │ │\n118: │   └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n119: │                                                                            │\n120: │   4. Download Results                                                      │\n121: │   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n122: │   │  client.download_file(\"/workspace/report.json\", \"report.json\")       │ │\n123: │   └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n124: │                                                                            │\n125: │   5. Cleanup                                                               │\n126: │   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n127: │   │  client.stop()  # or context manager exit                            │ │\n128: │   └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n129: │                                                                            │\n130: └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n131: ```\n132: \n133: ---\n134: \n135: ## Data Structures\n136: \n137: ### Configuration\n138: \n139: ```python\n140: from dataclasses import dataclass\n141: from typing import Optional\n142: \n143: @dataclass\n144: class AnalyzerConfig:\n145:     router_url: Optional[str] = None\n146:     workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None\n147:     namespace: str = \"default\"\n148:     session_name: str = \"pcap-analyzer\"\n149:     ttl: int = 3600\n150:     timeout: int = 120\n151:     verbose: bool = False\n152:     output_format: str = \"json\"\n153: ```\n154: \n155: ### Analysis Result Types\n156: \n157: ```python\n158: from dataclasses import dataclass\n159: from datetime import datetime\n160: from typing import List, Dict, Any\n161: \n162: @dataclass\n163: class PacketSummary:\n164:     timestamp: datetime\n165:     source_ip: str\n166:     source_port: int\n167:     dest_ip: str\n168:     dest_port: int\n169:     protocol: str\n170:     length: int\n171:     flags: Optional[str] = None\n172: \n173: @dataclass\n174: class TCPStream:\n175:     stream_id: int\n176:     packets: List[PacketSummary]\n177:     bytes_sent: int\n178:     bytes_recv: int\n179:     duration_ms: float\n180:     state: str\n181: \n182: @dataclass\n183: class HTTPTransaction:\n184:     request_time: datetime\n185:     method: str\n186:     url: str\n187:     host: str\n188:     response_code: int\n189:     response_time_ms: float\n190:     content_length: int\n191: \n192: @dataclass\n193: class AnalysisReport:\n194:     pcap_file: str\n195:     analysis_time: datetime\n196:     total_packets: int\n197:     protocols: Dict[str, int]\n198:     tcp_streams: List[TCPStream]\n199:     http_transactions: List[HTTPTransaction]\n200:     top_sources: List[Dict[str, Any]]\n201:     top_destinations: List[Dict[str, Any]]\n202:     anomalies: List[Dict[str, Any]]\n203: ```\n204: \n205: ---\n206: \n207: ## API Contracts\n208: \n209: ### Analyzer Interface\n210: \n211: ```python\n212: from abc import ABC, abstractmethod\n213: from typing import Optional, List\n214: from pathlib import Path\n215: \n216: class PCAPAnalyzerInterface(ABC):\n217:     @abstractmethod\n218:     def load_pcap(self, file_path: Path) -> None:\n219:         pass\n220:     \n221:     @abstractmethod\n222:     def get_packet_summary(self) -> List[PacketSummary]:\n223:         pass\n224:     \n225:     @abstractmethod\n226:     def get_tcp_streams(self) -> List[TCPStream]:\n227:         pass\n228:     \n229:     @abstractmethod\n230:     def get_http_transactions(self) -> List[HTTPTransaction]:\n231:         pass\n232:     \n233:     @abstractmethod\n234:     def generate_report(self, output_format: str = \"json\") -> str:\n235:         pass\n236: ```\n237: \n238: ### Analyzer Implementation\n239: \n240: ```python\n241: from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n242: \n243: class PCAPAnalyzer(PCAPAnalyzerInterface):\n244:     def __init__(self, config: AnalyzerConfig):\n245:         self.config = config\n246:         self._client: Optional[CodeInterpreterClient] = None\n247:     \n248:     def connect(self) -> None:\n249:         self._client = CodeInterpreterClient(\n250:             name=self.config.session_name,\n251:             namespace=self.config.namespace,\n252:             ttl=self.config.ttl,\n253:             router_url=self.config.router_url,\n254:             workload_manager_url=self.config.workload_manager_url,\n255:             verbose=self.config.verbose,\n256:         )\n257:         self._client.__enter__()\n258:     \n259:     def disconnect(self) -> None:\n260:         if self._client:\n261:             self._client.stop()\n262:             self._client = None\n263:     \n264:     def load_pcap(self, file_path: Path) -> None:\n265:         if not self._client:\n266:             raise RuntimeError(\"Not connected\")\n267:         self._client.upload_file(\n268:             str(file_path),\n269:             f\"/workspace/{file_path.name}\"\n270:         )\n271:         self._pcap_remote_path = f\"/workspace/{file_path.name}\"\n272:     \n273:     def get_packet_summary(self) -> List[PacketSummary]:\n274:         script = '''\n275: import json\n276: from scapy.all import rdpcap\n277: \n278: packets = rdpcap(\"{pcap_path}\")\n279: summary = []\n280: for pkt in packets:\n281:     if hasattr(pkt, 'IP'):\n282:         summary.append({\n283:             \"timestamp\": float(pkt.time),\n284:             \"source_ip\": pkt.IP.src,\n285:             \"dest_ip\": pkt.IP.dst,\n286:             \"protocol\": pkt.IP.proto,\n287:             \"length\": len(pkt)\n288:         })\n289: print(json.dumps(summary))\n290: '''\n291:         result = self._client.run_code(\n292:             \"python\",\n293:             script.format(pcap_path=self._pcap_remote_path),\n294:             timeout=self.config.timeout\n295:         )\n296:         return self._parse_summary(result)\n297:     \n298:     def get_tcp_streams(self) -> List[TCPStream]:\n299:         result = self._client.execute_command(\n300:             f\"tshark -r {self._pcap_remote_path} -z conv,tcp\",\n301:             timeout=self.config.timeout\n302:         )\n303:         return self._parse_tcp_conversations(result)\n304:     \n305:     def get_http_transactions(self) -> List[HTTPTransaction]:\n306:         result = self._client.execute_command(\n307:             f\"tshark -r {self._pcap_remote_path} -Y http -T fields \"\n308:             \"-e frame.time -e http.request.method -e http.host \"\n309:             \"-e http.request.uri -e http.response.code\",\n310:             timeout=self.config.timeout\n311:         )\n312:         return self._parse_http(result)\n313:     \n314:     def generate_report(self, output_format: str = \"json\") -> str:\n315:         report = AnalysisReport(\n316:             pcap_file=self._pcap_remote_path,\n317:             analysis_time=datetime.now(),\n318:             total_packets=len(self.get_packet_summary()),\n319:             protocols=self._get_protocol_stats(),\n320:             tcp_streams=self.get_tcp_streams(),\n321:             http_transactions=self.get_http_transactions(),\n322:             top_sources=self._get_top_sources(),\n323:             top_destinations=self._get_top_destinations(),\n324:             anomalies=self._detect_anomalies(),\n325:         )\n326:         \n327:         if output_format == \"json\":\n328:             return json.dumps(asdict(report), indent=2)\n329:         elif output_format == \"html\":\n330:             return self._generate_html_report(report)\n331:         else:\n332:             raise ValueError(f\"Unsupported format: {output_format}\")\n333: ```\n334: \n335: ### CLI Interface\n336: \n337: ```python\n338: import typer\n339: \n340: app = typer.Typer()\n341: \n342: @app.command()\n343: def analyze(\n344:     pcap_file: Path = typer.Argument(..., help=\"PCAP file to analyze\"),\n345:     router_url: str = typer.Option(None, help=\"Router URL\"),\n346:     output_format: str = typer.Option(\"json\", help=\"Output format (json/html)\"),\n347:     output_file: Path = typer.Option(None, help=\"Output file path\"),\n348:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, help=\"Verbose output\"),\n349: ):\n350:     config = AnalyzerConfig(\n351:         router_url=router_url,\n352:         verbose=verbose,\n353:         output_format=output_format,\n354:     )\n355:     \n356:     analyzer = PCAPAnalyzer(config)\n357:     try:\n358:         analyzer.connect()\n359:         analyzer.load_pcap(pcap_file)\n360:         report = analyzer.generate_report(output_format)\n361:         \n362:         if output_file:\n363:             output_file.write_text(report)\n364:         else:\n365:             print(report)\n366:     finally:\n367:         analyzer.disconnect()\n368: \n369: @app.command()\n370: def streams(\n371:     pcap_file: Path = typer.Argument(..., help=\"PCAP file\"),\n372:     router_url: str = typer.Option(None, help=\"Router URL\"),\n373: ):\n374:     config = AnalyzerConfig(router_url=router_url)\n375:     analyzer = PCAPAnalyzer(config)\n376:     try:\n377:         analyzer.connect()\n378:         analyzer.load_pcap(pcap_file)\n379:         streams = analyzer.get_tcp_streams()\n380:         for stream in streams:\n381:             print(f\"Stream {stream.stream_id}: {stream.bytes_sent}/{stream.bytes_recv} bytes\")\n382:     finally:\n383:         analyzer.disconnect()\n384: \n385: if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n386:     app()\n387: ```\n388: \n389: ---\n390: \n391: ## Error Handling\n392: \n393: ### Exception Classes\n394: \n395: ```python\n396: class AnalyzerError(Exception):\n397:     pass\n398: \n399: class ConnectionError(AnalyzerError):\n400:     def __init__(self, message: str, original_error: Exception):\n401:         super().__init__(f\"Connection failed: {message}\")\n402:         self.original_error = original_error\n403: \n404: class PCAPParseError(AnalyzerError):\n405:     def __init__(self, pcap_file: str, detail: str):\n406:         super().__init__(f\"Failed to parse {pcap_file}: {detail}\")\n407:         self.pcap_file = pcap_file\n408: \n409: class ToolNotAvailableError(AnalyzerError):\n410:     def __init__(self, tool_name: str):\n411:         super().__init__(f\"Required tool '{tool_name}' not available in sandbox\")\n412:         self.tool_name = tool_name\n413: \n414: class TimeoutError(AnalyzerError):\n415:     def __init__(self, operation: str, timeout_seconds: int):\n416:         super().__init__(f\"Operation '{operation}' timed out after {timeout_seconds}s\")\n417:         self.operation = operation\n418: ```\n419: \n420: ### Error Handling Pattern\n421: \n422: ```python\n423: def safe_analyze(analyzer: PCAPAnalyzer, pcap_file: Path) -> Optional[AnalysisReport]:\n424:     try:\n425:         analyzer.connect()\n426:         analyzer.load_pcap(pcap_file)\n427:         return analyzer.generate_report()\n428:     except ConnectionError as e:\n429:         logger.error(f\"Failed to connect to sandbox: {e}\")\n430:         return None\n431:     except PCAPParseError as e:\n432:         logger.error(f\"Invalid PCAP file: {e}\")\n433:         return None\n434:     except ToolNotAvailableError as e:\n435:         logger.error(f\"Sandbox missing tool: {e.tool_name}\")\n436:         logger.info(\"Ensure sandbox image includes tshark, tcpdump, scapy\")\n437:         return None\n438:     except TimeoutError as e:\n439:         logger.warning(f\"Analysis took too long, try larger timeout\")\n440:         return None\n441:     finally:\n442:         analyzer.disconnect()\n443: ```\n444: \n445: ---\n446: \n447: ## Testing Strategy\n448: \n449: ### Unit Tests\n450: \n451: ```python\n452: import pytest\n453: from unittest.mock import Mock, patch, MagicMock\n454: \n455: class TestPCAPAnalyzer:\n456:     @pytest.fixture\n457:     def mock_client(self):\n458:         client = Mock(spec=CodeInterpreterClient)\n459:         client.__enter__ = Mock(return_value=client)\n460:         client.__exit__ = Mock(return_value=False)\n461:         return client\n462:     \n463:     @pytest.fixture\n464:     def analyzer(self, mock_client):\n465:         config = AnalyzerConfig(router_url=\"http://router:8080\")\n466:         analyzer = PCAPAnalyzer(config)\n467:         analyzer._client = mock_client\n468:         return analyzer\n469:     \n470:     def test_load_pcap_success(self, analyzer, mock_client):\n471:         pcap_path = Path(\"test.pcap\")\n472:         analyzer.load_pcap(pcap_path)\n473:         mock_client.upload_file.assert_called_once_with(\n474:             \"test.pcap\", \"/workspace/test.pcap\"\n475:         )\n476:     \n477:     def test_get_packet_summary(self, analyzer, mock_client):\n478:         mock_client.run_code.return_value = json.dumps([\n479:             {\"timestamp\": 1234.5, \"source_ip\": \"10.0.0.1\", \n480:              \"dest_ip\": \"10.0.0.2\", \"protocol\": 6, \"length\": 100}\n481:         ])\n482:         \n483:         summary = analyzer.get_packet_summary()\n484:         assert len(summary) == 1\n485:         assert summary[0].source_ip == \"10.0.0.1\"\n486:     \n487:     def test_not_connected_raises(self):\n488:         analyzer = PCAPAnalyzer(AnalyzerConfig())\n489:         with pytest.raises(RuntimeError, match=\"Not connected\"):\n490:             analyzer.load_pcap(Path(\"test.pcap\"))\n491:     \n492:     def test_context_manager_cleanup(self):\n493:         config = AnalyzerConfig(router_url=\"http://router:8080\")\n494:         with PCAPAnalyzer(config) as analyzer:\n495:             analyzer.load_pcap(Path(\"test.pcap\"))\n496:         assert analyzer._client is None\n497: ```\n498: \n499: ### Integration Tests\n500: \n501: ```python\n502: import pytest\n503: import subprocess\n504: import time\n505: import requests\n506: \n507: @pytest.fixture(scope=\"module\")\n508: def sandbox_environment():\n509:     subprocess.run([\"kubectl\", \"apply\", \"-f\", \"sandbox.yaml\"])\n510:     time.sleep(30)\n511:     yield\n512:     subprocess.run([\"kubectl\", \"delete\", \"-f\", \"sandbox.yaml\"])\n513: \n514: class TestPCAPAnalyzerIntegration:\n515:     def test_real_pcap_analysis(self, sandbox_environment, tmp_path):\n516:         pcap_file = tmp_path / \"sample.pcap\"\n517:         pcap_file.write_bytes(SAMPLE_PCAP_DATA)\n518:         \n519:         config = AnalyzerConfig(\n520:             router_url=\"http://router.default.svc:8080\",\n521:             ttl=600,\n522:         )\n523:         \n524:         analyzer = PCAPAnalyzer(config)\n525:         analyzer.connect()\n526:         analyzer.load_pcap(pcap_file)\n527:         \n528:         summary = analyzer.get_packet_summary()\n529:         assert len(summary) > 0\n530:         \n531:         streams = analyzer.get_tcp_streams()\n532:         assert len(streams) >= 0\n533:         \n534:         analyzer.disconnect()\n535:     \n536:     def test_large_pcap_timeout(self, sandbox_environment, tmp_path):\n537:         large_pcap = create_large_pcap(tmp_path, 10000)\n538:         \n539:         config = AnalyzerConfig(\n540:             router_url=\"http://router.default.svc:8080\",\n541:             timeout=30,\n542:         )\n543:         \n544:         analyzer = PCAPAnalyzer(config)\n545:         analyzer.connect()\n546:         analyzer.load_pcap(large_pcap)\n547:         \n548:         with pytest.raises(TimeoutError):\n549:             analyzer.get_packet_summary()\n550:         \n551:         analyzer.disconnect()\n552: ```\n553: \n554: ### End-to-End Tests\n555: \n556: ```python\n557: class TestCLI:\n558:     def test_analyze_command(self, tmp_path):\n559:         pcap_file = tmp_path / \"test.pcap\"\n560:         output_file = tmp_path / \"report.json\"\n561:         \n562:         result = subprocess.run([\n563:             \"python\", \"-m\", \"pcap_analyzer\", \"analyze\",\n564:             str(pcap_file),\n565:             \"--router-url\", \"http://localhost:8080\",\n566:             \"--output-file\", str(output_file),\n567:         ], capture_output=True)\n568:         \n569:         assert result.returncode == 0\n570:         assert output_file.exists()\n571:         report = json.loads(output_file.read_text())\n572:         assert \"total_packets\" in report\n573: ```\n574: \n575: ---\n576: \n577: ## Dependencies\n578: \n579: ### requirements.txt\n580: \n581: ```text\n582: agentcube-sdk>=1.0.0\n583: typer>=0.9.0\n584: pydantic>=2.0.0\n585: rich>=13.0.0\n586: ```\n587: \n588: ### Sandbox Image Requirements\n589: \n590: The sandbox pod image must include:\n591: \n592: ```text\n593: tshark>=4.0.0\n594: tcpdump>=4.9.0\n595: python3>=3.10\n596: scapy>=2.5.0\n597: pyshark>=0.4.3\n598: ```\n599: \n600: ---\n601: \n602: ## Configuration\n603: \n604: ### Environment Variables\n605: \n606: | Variable | Default | Purpose |\n607: |----------|---------|---------|\n608: | `ROUTER_URL` | None | Router endpoint URL |\n609: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | None | Workload manager URL |\n610: | `ANALYZER_NAMESPACE` | default | Kubernetes namespace |\n611: | `ANALYZER_TTL` | 3600 | Session TTL in seconds |\n612: | `ANALYZER_TIMEOUT` | 120 | Analysis timeout in seconds |\n613: \n614: ### CLI Options\n615: \n616: | Option | Default | Purpose |\n617: |--------|---------|---------|\n618: | `--router-url` | None | Router URL override |\n619: | `--namespace` | default | Namespace override |\n620: | `--ttl` | 3600 | Session TTL |\n621: | `--timeout` | 120 | Operation timeout |\n622: | `--output-format` | json | Output format (json/html) |\n623: | `--verbose` | False | Enable debug logging |\n624: \n625: ---\n626: \n627: ## Implementation Checklist\n628: \n629: - [ ] `example/pcap-analyzer/main.py` - CLI entry point\n630: - [ ] `example/pcap-analyzer/analyzer.py` - Core analyzer class\n631: - [ ] `example/pcap-analyzer/parsers/tcp_parser.py` - TCP stream parser\n632: - [ ] `example/pcap-analyzer/parsers/http_parser.py` - HTTP transaction parser\n633: - [ ] `example/pcap-analyzer/parsers/dns_parser.py` - DNS query parser\n634: - [ ] `example/pcap-analyzer/utils/file_utils.py` - File utilities\n635: - [ ] `example/pcap-analyzer/utils/report_utils.py` - Report generation\n636: - [ ] `example/pcap-analyzer/requirements.txt` - Dependencies\n637: - [ ] `example/pcap-analyzer/README.md` - Usage documentation\n638: - [ ] `example/pcap-analyzer/tests/test_analyzer.py` - Analyzer tests\n639: - [ ] `example/pcap-analyzer/tests/test_parsers.py` - Parser tests\n640: - [ ] `example/pcap-analyzer/sample_data/sample.pcap` - Test data\n641: - [ ] Integration test with real sandbox\n642: - [ ] Documentation with usage examples\n643: \n644: ---\n645: \n646: ## Metrics\n647: \n648: ### Performance Targets\n649: \n650: | Metric | Target |\n651: |--------|--------|\n652: | Small PCAP (<1000 packets) analysis | < 5s |\n653: | Medium PCAP (1000-10000 packets) | < 30s |\n654: | Large PCAP (>10000 packets) | < 120s |\n655: | Memory usage in sandbox | < 512MB |\n656: \n657: ### Observability\n658: \n659: ```python\n660: import time\n661: from functools import wraps\n662: \n663: def timed_operation(operation_name: str):\n664:     def decorator(func):\n665:         @wraps(func)\n666:         def wrapper(*args, **kwargs):\n667:             start = time.time()\n668:             try:\n669:                 result = func(*args, **kwargs)\n670:                 duration = time.time() - start\n671:                 logger.info(f\"{operation_name} completed in {duration:.2f}s\")\n672:                 return result\n673:             except Exception as e:\n674:                 duration = time.time() - start\n675:                 logger.error(f\"{operation_name} failed after {duration:.2f}s: {e}\")\n676:                 raise\n677:         return wrapper\n678:     return decorator\n679: ```\n680: \n681: ---\n682: \n683: ## Security Considerations\n684: \n685: ### Sandbox Isolation\n686: \n687: - All PCAP analysis runs in isolated sandbox pod\n688: - No direct filesystem access from analyzer host\n689: - Network tools confined to sandbox network namespace\n690: \n691: ### Data Handling\n692: \n693: - PCAP files uploaded via secure channel (HTTPS)\n694: - Session-based authentication via `x-agentcube-session-id`\n695: - Automatic cleanup of uploaded files on session termination\n696: \n697: ### Resource Limits\n698: \n699: - Maximum PCAP file size: configurable via SDK\n700: - Maximum execution time: configurable timeout\n701: - Memory limits enforced by sandbox pod spec\n702: \n703: ---\n704: \n705: ## Example Usage\n706: \n707: ### Basic Analysis\n708: \n709: ```python\n710: from pcap_analyzer import PCAPAnalyzer, AnalyzerConfig\n711: \n712: config = AnalyzerConfig(router_url=\"http://router.example.com:8080\")\n713: \n714: with PCAPAnalyzer(config) as analyzer:\n715:     analyzer.load_pcap(\"network_traffic.pcap\")\n716:     \n717:     print(f\"Total packets: {len(analyzer.get_packet_summary())}\")\n718:     \n719:     for stream in analyzer.get_tcp_streams():\n720:         print(f\"TCP Stream {stream.stream_id}: {stream.state}\")\n721:     \n722:     report = analyzer.generate_report()\n723:     print(report)\n724: ```\n725: \n726: ### CLI Usage\n727: \n728: ```bash\n729: # Analyze a PCAP file\n730: python -m pcap_analyzer analyze traffic.pcap \\\n731:     --router-url http://router:8080 \\\n732:     --output-format json \\\n733:     --output-file report.json\n734: \n735: # List TCP streams\n736: python -m pcap_analyzer streams traffic.pcap \\\n737:     --router-url http://router:8080\n738: \n739: # Verbose analysis\n740: python -m pcap_analyzer analyze traffic.pcap \\\n741:     --router-url http://router:8080 \\\n742:     --verbose\n743: ```\n\n(End of file - total 743 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-037: PCAP Analyzer Example Application\n\n## Overview\n\nA Python example application demonstrating AgentCube SDK usage for PCAP (packet capture) file analysis. The application uses `CodeInterpreterClient` to execute network analysis tools and Python scripts in an isolated sandbox environment.\n\n| Attribute | Value |\n|-----------|-------|\n| Module | example |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n| SDK | agentcube-sdk |\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Directory Structure\n\n```","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/example/design.md","time":{"start":1775895040657,"end":1775895040679}}}}
