{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775895040698,"sessionID":"ses_28468a2b8ffeCdGYvhIGS4WTXI","part":{"id":"prt_d7b97cbbb0016XxXjbD6kuO6DE","messageID":"msg_d7b97acae001WxkXj5RiY5xiH8","sessionID":"ses_28468a2b8ffeCdGYvhIGS4WTXI","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-f458f7c368cb4a18bbeae84c97085d0e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/example/pcap-analyzer/README.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/example/pcap-analyzer/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # PCAP Analyzer\n2: \n3: A Python example application demonstrating AgentCube SDK usage for PCAP (packet capture) file analysis.\n4: \n5: ## Overview\n6: \n7: This application uses `CodeInterpreterClient` to execute network analysis tools and Python scripts in an isolated sandbox environment. It demonstrates:\n8: \n9: - Session lifecycle management with AgentCube SDK\n10: - File upload/download operations\n11: - Command execution in sandbox\n12: - Code execution with Python runtime\n13: - Integration with network analysis tools (tshark, scapy)\n14: \n15: ## Installation\n16: \n17: ```bash\n18: pip install -r requirements.txt\n19: ```\n20: \n21: ## Usage\n22: \n23: ### CLI Commands\n24: \n25: ```bash\n26: # Analyze a PCAP file and generate a report\n27: python -m pcap_analyzer analyze traffic.pcap \\\n28:     --router-url http://router:8080 \\\n29:     --output-format json \\\n30:     --output-file report.json\n31: \n32: # List TCP streams\n33: python -m pcap_analyzer streams traffic.pcap \\\n34:     --router-url http://router:8080\n35: \n36: # List HTTP transactions\n37: python -m pcap_analyzer http traffic.pcap \\\n38:     --router-url http://router:8080\n39: \n40: # List DNS queries\n41: python -m pcap_analyzer dns traffic.pcap \\\n42:     --router-url http://router:8080\n43: \n44: # Show packet summary\n45: python -m pcap_analyzer summary traffic.pcap \\\n46:     --router-url http://router:8080\n47: \n48: # Verbose analysis\n49: python -m pcap_analyzer analyze traffic.pcap \\\n50:     --router-url http://router:8080 \\\n51:     --verbose\n52: ```\n53: \n54: ### Python API\n55: \n56: ```python\n57: from pcap_analyzer import PCAPAnalyzer, AnalyzerConfig\n58: \n59: config = AnalyzerConfig(router_url=\"http://router.example.com:8080\")\n60: \n61: with PCAPAnalyzer(config) as analyzer:\n62:     analyzer.load_pcap(\"network_traffic.pcap\")\n63:     \n64:     # Get packet summary\n65:     packets = analyzer.get_packet_summary()\n66:     print(f\"Total packets: {len(packets)}\")\n67:     \n68:     # Get TCP streams\n69:     for stream in analyzer.get_tcp_streams():\n70:         print(f\"TCP Stream {stream.stream_id}: {stream.state}\")\n71:     \n72:     # Get HTTP transactions\n73:     for trans in analyzer.get_http_transactions():\n74:         print(f\"{trans.method} {trans.host}{trans.url} -> {trans.response_code}\")\n75:     \n76:     # Generate full report\n77:     report = analyzer.generate_report(output_format=\"json\")\n78:     print(report)\n79: ```\n80: \n81: ## Configuration\n82: \n83: ### Environment Variables\n84: \n85: | Variable | Default | Purpose |\n86: |----------|---------|---------|\n87: | `ROUTER_URL` | None | Router endpoint URL (required) |\n88: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | None | Workload manager URL |\n89: | `ANALYZER_NAMESPACE` | default | Kubernetes namespace |\n90: | `ANALYZER_TTL` | 3600 | Session TTL in seconds |\n91: | `ANALYZER_TIMEOUT` | 120 | Analysis timeout in seconds |\n92: \n93: ### CLI Options\n94: \n95: | Option | Default | Purpose |\n96: |--------|---------|---------|\n97: | `--router-url` | None | Router URL override |\n98: | `--wm-url` | None | Workload manager URL |\n99: | `--namespace` | default | Namespace override |\n100: | `--ttl` | 3600 | Session TTL |\n101: | `--timeout` | 120 | Operation timeout |\n102: | `--format` | json | Output format (json/html/text) |\n103: | `--output` | None | Output file path |\n104: | `--verbose` | False | Enable debug logging |\n105: \n106: ## Output Formats\n107: \n108: ### JSON Report\n109: \n110: ```json\n111: {\n112:   \"pcap_file\": \"traffic.pcap\",\n113:   \"analysis_time\": \"2024-01-15T10:30:00\",\n114:   \"total_packets\": 1500,\n115:   \"protocols\": {\"TCP\": 1200, \"UDP\": 200, \"ICMP\": 100},\n116:   \"tcp_streams\": [...],\n117:   \"http_transactions\": [...],\n118:   \"dns_queries\": [...],\n119:   \"top_sources\": [...],\n120:   \"top_destinations\": [...],\n121:   \"anomalies\": [...]\n122: }\n123: ```\n124: \n125: ### HTML Report\n126: \n127: Generates a styled HTML page with tables and visualizations.\n128: \n129: ### Text Summary\n130: \n131: Plain text summary with key statistics.\n132: \n133: ## Sandbox Requirements\n134: \n135: The sandbox pod image must include:\n136: \n137: - `tshark>=4.0.0` - Wireshark CLI tool\n138: - `tcpdump>=4.9.0` - Packet capture tool\n139: - `python3>=3.10` - Python runtime\n140: - `scapy>=2.5.0` - Packet manipulation library\n141: \n142: ## Error Handling\n143: \n144: | Error Type | Description | Resolution |\n145: |------------|-------------|------------|\n146: | `ConnectionError` | Failed to connect to sandbox | Check router URL and network |\n147: | `PCAPParseError` | Invalid PCAP file | Verify file format |\n148: | `ToolNotAvailableError` | Required tool missing | Update sandbox image |\n149: | `TimeoutError` | Operation exceeded timeout | Increase timeout value |\n150: \n151: ## Performance\n152: \n153: | Metric | Target |\n154: |--------|--------|\n155: | Small PCAP (<1000 packets) | < 5s |\n156: | Medium PCAP (1000-10000) | < 30s |\n157: | Large PCAP (>10000) | < 120s |\n158: | Memory usage | < 512MB |\n159: \n160: ## Testing\n161: \n162: ```bash\n163: pytest tests/\n164: ```\n165: \n166: ## License\n167: \n168: Part of AgentCube project.\n\n(End of file - total 168 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# PCAP Analyzer\n\nA Python example application demonstrating AgentCube SDK usage for PCAP (packet capture) file analysis.\n\n## Overview\n\nThis application uses `CodeInterpreterClient` to execute network analysis tools and Python scripts in an isolated sandbox environment. It demonstrates:\n\n- Session lifecycle management with AgentCube SDK\n- File upload/download operations\n- Command execution in sandbox\n- Code execution with Python runtime\n- Integration with network analysis tools (tshark, scapy)\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\npip install -r requirements.txt\n```\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/example/pcap-analyzer/README.md","time":{"start":1775895040653,"end":1775895040695}}}}
