nner.stop` cleans up sessions\n923: - [ ] PLANNER agent generates executable Python scripts\n924: - [ ] `_analyze_with_retries` retries on execution failure\n925: - [ ] REPORTER agent synthesizes results into report\n926: - [ ] Environment defaults match constants table\n927: - [ ] Dockerfile uses `uv` and vendors SDK\n928: - [ ] Deployment manifest sets resources and secrets correctly\n929: - [ ] `AnalyzeResponse` schema matches endpoint output\n930: - [ ] All Python files pass syntax check\n931: - [ ] All YAML files parse correctly\n932: - [ ] All unit tests pass\n933: \n934: ---\n935: \n936: ## File Changes Summary\n937: \n938: | File | Action | Lines | Description |\n939: |------|--------|-------|-------------|\n940: | `example/pcap-analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py` | Create | ~200 | FastAPI app with SandboxRunner, agents, /analyze endpoint |\n941: | `example/pcap-analyzer/requirements.txt` | Create | ~10 | LangChain, FastAPI, and supporting dependencies |\n942: | `example/pcap-analyzer/Dockerfile` | Create | ~15 | `uv`-based image with vendored SDK |\n943: | `example/pcap-analyzer/deployment.yaml` | Create | ~60 | K8s Deployment with Secret and env wiring |\n944: | `example/pcap-analyzer/README.md` | Create | ~80 | Usage and deployment documentation |\n945: | `example/pcap-analyzer/parsers/__init__.py` | Create | ~5 | Parser package marker |\n946: | `example/pcap-analyzer/parsers/tcp_parser.py` | Create | ~40 | TCP stream parser |\n947: | `example/pcap-analyzer/parsers/http_parser.py` | Create | ~40 | HTTP transaction parser |\n948: | `example/pcap-analyzer/parsers/dns_parser.py` | Create | ~30 | DNS query parser |\n949: | `example/pcap-analyzer/utils/__init__.py` | Create | ~5 | Utility package marker |\n950: | `example/pcap-analyzer/utils/file_utils.py` | Create | ~30 | File handling utilities |\n951: | `example/pcap-analyzer/utils/report_utils.py` | Create | ~40 | Report generation utilities |\n952: | `example/pcap-analyzer/sample_data/sample.pcap` | Create | ~50KB | Sample PCAP file |\n953: | `example/pcap-analyzer/sample_data/expected_output.json` | Create | ~50 | Expected analysis output |\n954: | `example/pcap-analyzer/tests/__init__.py` | Create | ~5 | Test package marker |\n955: | `example/pcap-analyzer/tests/test_analyzer.py` | Create | ~80 | Analyzer unit tests |\n956: | `example/pcap-analyzer/tests/test_parsers.py` | Create | ~50 | Parser unit tests |\n957: | `example/pcap-analyzer/tests/test_integration.py` | Create | ~40 | Integration tests |\n958: | `example/pcap-analyzer/tests/conftest.py` | Create | ~50 | Test fixtures |\n959: \n960: **Total: 20 files, ~580 lines + 50KB data**\n961: \n962: ---\n963: \n964: ## Implementation Notes\n965: \n966: - **Design completed at Stage ST-3**\n967: - **FastAPI pattern**: Startup validation, async endpoints, Pydantic models\n968: - **SandboxRunner**: Wrapper class for `CodeInterpreterClient` with upload and run methods\n969: - **LangGraph agents**: ReAct pattern for planner (script generation) and reporter (report synthesis)\n970: - **Retry logic**: `_analyze_with_retries` calls `_repair_script` on execution failure, retries up to `MAX_RETRIES`\n971: - **Container pattern**: uv base image, vendored SDK, `PYTHONPATH=/app`\n972: - **K8s deployment**: Secret for API key, env for AgentCube URLs, resource limits\n973: - **Test strategy**: Mock `CodeInterpreterClient`, `TestClient` for FastAPI, integration tests require live backend\n974: - **Parser modules**: TCP stream, HTTP transaction, DNS query parsing from tshark output\n975: - **Sample data**: ~50KB PCAP file with ~100 packets for testing\n976: \n977: ---\n978: \n979: ## Implementation Timeline\n980: \n981: | Phase | Tasks | Status | Completion |\n982: |-------|-------|--------|------------|\n983: | Phase 1: Directory Structure | T1.1-T1.5 | Pending | 0% |\n984: | Phase 2: Configuration Constants | T2.1-T2.9 | Pending | 0% |\n985: | Phase 3: Environment Loading | T3.1-T3.8 | Pending | 0% |\n986: | Phase 4: SandboxRunner | T4.